80// could go into QTextCursor...
81static QTextLine currentTextLine(const QTextCursor &cursor)
82{
83 const QTextBlock block = cursor.block();
84 if (!block.isValid())
85 return QTextLine();
86
87 const QTextLayout *layout = block.layout();
88 if (!layout)
89 return QTextLine();
90
91 const int relativePos = cursor.position() - block.position();
92 return layout->lineForTextPosition(pos: relativePos);
93}

122bool QWidgetTextControlPrivate::cursorMoveKeyEvent(QKeyEvent *e)
123{
124#ifdef QT_NO_SHORTCUT
125 Q_UNUSED(e);
126#endif
127
128 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
129 if (cursor.isNull())
130 return false;
131
132 const QTextCursor oldSelection = cursor;
133 const int oldCursorPos = cursor.position();
134
135 QTextCursor::MoveMode mode = QTextCursor::MoveAnchor;
136 QTextCursor::MoveOperation op = QTextCursor::NoMove;
137
138 if (false) {
139 }
140#ifndef QT_NO_SHORTCUT
141 if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToNextChar) {
142 op = QTextCursor::Right;
143 }
144 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToPreviousChar) {
145 op = QTextCursor::Left;
146 }
147 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectNextChar) {
148 op = QTextCursor::Right;
149 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
150 }
151 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectPreviousChar) {
152 op = QTextCursor::Left;
153 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
154 }
155 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectNextWord) {
156 op = QTextCursor::WordRight;
157 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
158 }
159 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectPreviousWord) {
160 op = QTextCursor::WordLeft;
161 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
162 }
163 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectStartOfLine) {
164 op = QTextCursor::StartOfLine;
165 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
166 }
167 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectEndOfLine) {
168 op = QTextCursor::EndOfLine;
169 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
170 }
171 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectStartOfBlock) {
172 op = QTextCursor::StartOfBlock;
173 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
174 }
175 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectEndOfBlock) {
176 op = QTextCursor::EndOfBlock;
177 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
178 }
179 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectStartOfDocument) {
180 op = QTextCursor::Start;
181 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
182 }
183 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectEndOfDocument) {
184 op = QTextCursor::End;
185 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
186 }
187 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectPreviousLine) {
188 op = QTextCursor::Up;
189 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
190 {
191 QTextBlock block = cursor.block();
192 QTextLine line = currentTextLine(cursor);
193 if (!block.previous().isValid()
194 && line.isValid()
195 && line.lineNumber() == 0)
196 op = QTextCursor::Start;
197 }
198 }
199 else if (e == QKeySequence::SelectNextLine) {
200 op = QTextCursor::Down;
201 mode = QTextCursor::KeepAnchor;
202 {
203 QTextBlock block = cursor.block();
204 QTextLine line = currentTextLine(cursor);
205 if (!block.next().isValid()
206 && line.isValid()
207 && line.lineNumber() == block.layout()->lineCount() - 1)
208 op = QTextCursor::End;
209 }
210 }
211 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToNextWord) {
212 op = QTextCursor::WordRight;
213 }
214 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToPreviousWord) {
215 op = QTextCursor::WordLeft;
216 }
217 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToEndOfBlock) {
218 op = QTextCursor::EndOfBlock;
219 }
220 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToStartOfBlock) {
221 op = QTextCursor::StartOfBlock;
222 }
223 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToNextLine) {
224 op = QTextCursor::Down;
225 }
226 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToPreviousLine) {
227 op = QTextCursor::Up;
228 }
229 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToStartOfLine) {
230 op = QTextCursor::StartOfLine;
231 }
232 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToEndOfLine) {
233 op = QTextCursor::EndOfLine;
234 }
235 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToStartOfDocument) {
236 op = QTextCursor::Start;
237 }
238 else if (e == QKeySequence::MoveToEndOfDocument) {
239 op = QTextCursor::End;
240 }
241#endif // QT_NO_SHORTCUT
242 else {
243 return false;
244 }
245
246// Except for pageup and pagedown, OS X has very different behavior, we don't do it all, but
247// here's the breakdown:
248// Shift still works as an anchor, but only one of the other keys can be down Ctrl (Command),
249// Alt (Option), or Meta (Control).
250// Command/Control + Left/Right -- Move to left or right of the line
251// + Up/Down -- Move to top bottom of the file. (Control doesn't move the cursor)
252// Option + Left/Right -- Move one word Left/right.
253// + Up/Down -- Begin/End of Paragraph.
254// Home/End Top/Bottom of file. (usually don't move the cursor, but will select)
255
256 bool visualNavigation = cursor.visualNavigation();
257 cursor.setVisualNavigation(true);
258 const bool moved = cursor.movePosition(op, mode);
259 cursor.setVisualNavigation(visualNavigation);
260 q->ensureCursorVisible();
261
262 bool ignoreNavigationEvents = ignoreUnusedNavigationEvents;
263 bool isNavigationEvent = e->key() == Qt::Key_Up || e->key() == Qt::Key_Down;
264
265#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
266 ignoreNavigationEvents = ignoreNavigationEvents || QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled();
267 isNavigationEvent = isNavigationEvent ||
268 (QApplication::navigationMode() == Qt::NavigationModeKeypadDirectional
269 && (e->key() == Qt::Key_Left || e->key() == Qt::Key_Right));
270#else
271 isNavigationEvent = isNavigationEvent || e->key() == Qt::Key_Left || e->key() == Qt::Key_Right;
272#endif
273
274 if (moved) {
275 if (cursor.position() != oldCursorPos)
276 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
277 emit q->microFocusChanged();
278 } else if (ignoreNavigationEvents && isNavigationEvent && oldSelection.anchor() == cursor.anchor()) {
279 return false;
280 }
281
282 selectionChanged(/*forceEmitSelectionChanged =*/(mode == QTextCursor::KeepAnchor));
283
284 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection);
285
286 return true;
287}

289void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::updateCurrentCharFormat()
290{
291 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
292
293 QTextCharFormat fmt = cursor.charFormat();
294 if (fmt == lastCharFormat)
295 return;
296 lastCharFormat = fmt;
297
298 emit q->currentCharFormatChanged(format: fmt);
299 emit q->microFocusChanged();
300}

302void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::indent()
303{
304 QTextBlockFormat blockFmt = cursor.blockFormat();
305
306 QTextList *list = cursor.currentList();
307 if (!list) {
308 QTextBlockFormat modifier;
309 modifier.setIndent(blockFmt.indent() + 1);
310 cursor.mergeBlockFormat(modifier);
311 } else {
312 QTextListFormat format = list->format();
313 format.setIndent(format.indent() + 1);
314
315 if (list->itemNumber(cursor.block()) == 1)
316 list->setFormat(format);
317 else
318 cursor.createList(format);
319 }
320}
321
322void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::outdent()
323{
324 QTextBlockFormat blockFmt = cursor.blockFormat();
325
326 QTextList *list = cursor.currentList();
327
328 if (!list) {
329 QTextBlockFormat modifier;
330 modifier.setIndent(blockFmt.indent() - 1);
331 cursor.mergeBlockFormat(modifier);
332 } else {
333 QTextListFormat listFmt = list->format();
334 listFmt.setIndent(listFmt.indent() - 1);
335 list->setFormat(listFmt);
336 }
337}

339void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::gotoNextTableCell()
340{
341 QTextTable *table = cursor.currentTable();
342 QTextTableCell cell = table->cellAt(c: cursor);
343
344 int newColumn = cell.column() + cell.columnSpan();
345 int newRow = cell.row();
346
347 if (newColumn >= table->columns()) {
348 newColumn = 0;
349 ++newRow;
350 if (newRow >= table->rows())
351 table->insertRows(pos: table->rows(), num: 1);
352 }
353
354 cell = table->cellAt(row: newRow, col: newColumn);
355 cursor = cell.firstCursorPosition();
356}
357
358void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::gotoPreviousTableCell()
359{
360 QTextTable *table = cursor.currentTable();
361 QTextTableCell cell = table->cellAt(c: cursor);
362
363 int newColumn = cell.column() - 1;
364 int newRow = cell.row();
365
366 if (newColumn < 0) {
367 newColumn = table->columns() - 1;
368 --newRow;
369 if (newRow < 0)
370 return;
371 }
372
373 cell = table->cellAt(row: newRow, col: newColumn);
374 cursor = cell.firstCursorPosition();
375}

377void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::createAutoBulletList()
378{
379 cursor.beginEditBlock();
380
381 QTextBlockFormat blockFmt = cursor.blockFormat();
382
383 QTextListFormat listFmt;
384 listFmt.setStyle(QTextListFormat::ListDisc);
385 listFmt.setIndent(blockFmt.indent() + 1);
386
387 blockFmt.setIndent(0);
388 cursor.setBlockFormat(blockFmt);
389
390 cursor.createList(format: listFmt);
391
392 cursor.endEditBlock();
393}

404void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::setContent(Qt::TextFormat format, const QString &text, QTextDocument *document)
405{
406 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
407
408 // for use when called from setPlainText. we may want to re-use the currently
409 // set char format then.
410 const QTextCharFormat charFormatForInsertion = cursor.charFormat();
411
412 bool clearDocument = true;
413 if (!doc) {
414 if (document) {
415 doc = document;
416 } else {
417 palette = QApplication::palette(className: "QWidgetTextControl");
418 doc = new QTextDocument(q);
419 }
420 clearDocument = false;
421 _q_documentLayoutChanged();
422 cursor = QTextCursor(doc);
423
424// #### doc->documentLayout()->setPaintDevice(viewport);
425
426 QObjectPrivate::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::contentsChanged, receiverPrivate: this,
427 slot: &QWidgetTextControlPrivate::_q_updateCurrentCharFormatAndSelection);
428 QObjectPrivate::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::cursorPositionChanged, receiverPrivate: this,
429 slot: &QWidgetTextControlPrivate::_q_emitCursorPosChanged);
430 QObjectPrivate::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::documentLayoutChanged, receiverPrivate: this,
431 slot: &QWidgetTextControlPrivate::_q_documentLayoutChanged);
432
433 // convenience signal forwards
434 QObject::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::undoAvailable, receiver: q, slot: &QWidgetTextControl::undoAvailable);
435 QObject::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::redoAvailable, receiver: q, slot: &QWidgetTextControl::redoAvailable);
436 QObject::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::modificationChanged, receiver: q,
437 slot: &QWidgetTextControl::modificationChanged);
438 QObject::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::blockCountChanged, receiver: q,
439 slot: &QWidgetTextControl::blockCountChanged);
440 }
441
442 bool previousUndoRedoState = doc->isUndoRedoEnabled();
443 if (!document)
444 doc->setUndoRedoEnabled(false);
445
446 //Saving the index save some time.
447 static int contentsChangedIndex = QMetaMethod::fromSignal(signal: &QTextDocument::contentsChanged).methodIndex();
448 static int textChangedIndex = QMetaMethod::fromSignal(signal: &QWidgetTextControl::textChanged).methodIndex();
449 // avoid multiple textChanged() signals being emitted
450 QMetaObject::disconnect(sender: doc, signal_index: contentsChangedIndex, receiver: q, method_index: textChangedIndex);
451
452 if (!text.isEmpty()) {
453 // clear 'our' cursor for insertion to prevent
454 // the emission of the cursorPositionChanged() signal.
455 // instead we emit it only once at the end instead of
456 // at the end of the document after loading and when
457 // positioning the cursor again to the start of the
458 // document.
459 cursor = QTextCursor();
460 if (format == Qt::PlainText) {
461 QTextCursor formatCursor(doc);
462 // put the setPlainText and the setCharFormat into one edit block,
463 // so that the syntax highlight triggers only /once/ for the entire
464 // document, not twice.
465 formatCursor.beginEditBlock();
466 doc->setPlainText(text);
467 doc->setUndoRedoEnabled(false);
468 formatCursor.select(selection: QTextCursor::Document);
469 formatCursor.setCharFormat(charFormatForInsertion);
470 formatCursor.endEditBlock();
471#if QT_CONFIG(textmarkdownreader)
472 } else if (format == Qt::MarkdownText) {
473 doc->setMarkdown(markdown: text);
474 doc->setUndoRedoEnabled(false);
475#endif
476 } else {
477#ifndef QT_NO_TEXTHTMLPARSER
478 doc->setHtml(text);
479#else
480 doc->setPlainText(text);
481#endif
482 doc->setUndoRedoEnabled(false);
483 }
484 cursor = QTextCursor(doc);
485 } else if (clearDocument) {
486 doc->clear();
487 }
488 cursor.setCharFormat(charFormatForInsertion);
489
490 QMetaObject::connect(sender: doc, signal_index: contentsChangedIndex, receiver: q, method_index: textChangedIndex);
491 emit q->textChanged();
492 if (!document)
493 doc->setUndoRedoEnabled(previousUndoRedoState);
494 _q_updateCurrentCharFormatAndSelection();
495 if (!document)
496 doc->setModified(false);
497
498 q->ensureCursorVisible();
499 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
500
501 QObjectPrivate::connect(sender: doc, signal: &QTextDocument::contentsChange, receiverPrivate: this,
502 slot: &QWidgetTextControlPrivate::_q_contentsChanged, type: Qt::UniqueConnection);
503}

505void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::startDrag()
506{
507#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
508 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
509 mousePressed = false;
510 if (!contextWidget)
511 return;
512 QMimeData *data = q->createMimeDataFromSelection();
513
514 QDrag *drag = new QDrag(contextWidget);
515 drag->setMimeData(data);
516
517 Qt::DropActions actions = Qt::CopyAction;
518 Qt::DropAction action;
519 if (interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable) {
520 actions |= Qt::MoveAction;
521 action = drag->exec(supportedActions: actions, defaultAction: Qt::MoveAction);
522 } else {
523 action = drag->exec(supportedActions: actions, defaultAction: Qt::CopyAction);
524 }
525
526 if (action == Qt::MoveAction && drag->target() != contextWidget)
527 cursor.removeSelectedText();
528#endif
529}

556void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::repaintOldAndNewSelection(const QTextCursor &oldSelection)
557{
558 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
559 if (cursor.hasSelection()
560 && oldSelection.hasSelection()
561 && cursor.currentFrame() == oldSelection.currentFrame()
562 && !cursor.hasComplexSelection()
563 && !oldSelection.hasComplexSelection()
564 && cursor.anchor() == oldSelection.anchor()
565 ) {
566 QTextCursor differenceSelection(doc);
567 differenceSelection.setPosition(pos: oldSelection.position());
568 differenceSelection.setPosition(pos: cursor.position(), mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
569 emit q->updateRequest(rect: q->selectionRect(cursor: differenceSelection));
570 } else {
571 if (!oldSelection.isNull())
572 emit q->updateRequest(rect: q->selectionRect(cursor: oldSelection) | cursorRectPlusUnicodeDirectionMarkers(cursor: oldSelection));
573 emit q->updateRequest(rect: q->selectionRect() | cursorRectPlusUnicodeDirectionMarkers(cursor));
574 }
575}

577void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::selectionChanged(bool forceEmitSelectionChanged /*=false*/)
578{
579 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
580 if (forceEmitSelectionChanged) {
581 emit q->selectionChanged();
582#if QT_CONFIG(accessibility)
583 if (q->parent() && q->parent()->isWidgetType()) {
584 QAccessibleTextSelectionEvent ev(q->parent(), cursor.anchor(), cursor.position());
585 QAccessible::updateAccessibility(event: &ev);
586 }
587#endif
588 }
589
590 if (cursor.position() == lastSelectionPosition
591 && cursor.anchor() == lastSelectionAnchor)
592 return;
593
594 bool selectionStateChange = (cursor.hasSelection()
595 != (lastSelectionPosition != lastSelectionAnchor));
596 if (selectionStateChange)
597 emit q->copyAvailable(b: cursor.hasSelection());
598
599 if (!forceEmitSelectionChanged
600 && (selectionStateChange
601 || (cursor.hasSelection()
602 && (cursor.position() != lastSelectionPosition
603 || cursor.anchor() != lastSelectionAnchor)))) {
604 emit q->selectionChanged();
605#if QT_CONFIG(accessibility)
606 if (q->parent() && q->parent()->isWidgetType()) {
607 QAccessibleTextSelectionEvent ev(q->parent(), cursor.anchor(), cursor.position());
608 QAccessible::updateAccessibility(event: &ev);
609 }
610#endif
611 }
612 emit q->microFocusChanged();
613 lastSelectionPosition = cursor.position();
614 lastSelectionAnchor = cursor.anchor();
615}

620 selectionChanged();
621}

644void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::_q_contentsChanged(int from, int charsRemoved, int charsAdded)
645{
646#if QT_CONFIG(accessibility)
647 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
648
649 if (QAccessible::isActive() && q->parent() && q->parent()->isWidgetType()) {
650 QTextCursor tmp(doc);
651 tmp.setPosition(pos: from);
652 // when setting a new text document the length is off
653 // QTBUG-32583 - characterCount is off by 1 requires the -1
654 tmp.setPosition(pos: qMin(a: doc->characterCount() - 1, b: from + charsAdded), mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
655 QString newText = tmp.selectedText();
656
657 // always report the right number of removed chars, but in lack of the real string use spaces
658 QString oldText = QString(charsRemoved, u' ');
659
660 QAccessibleEvent *ev = nullptr;
661 if (charsRemoved == 0) {
662 ev = new QAccessibleTextInsertEvent(q->parent(), from, newText);
663 } else if (charsAdded == 0) {
664 ev = new QAccessibleTextRemoveEvent(q->parent(), from, oldText);
665 } else {
666 ev = new QAccessibleTextUpdateEvent(q->parent(), from, oldText, newText);
667 }
668 QAccessible::updateAccessibility(event: ev);
669 delete ev;
670 }
671#else
672 Q_UNUSED(from);
673 Q_UNUSED(charsRemoved);
674 Q_UNUSED(charsAdded);
675#endif
676}

690void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::setCursorVisible(bool visible)
691{
692 if (cursorVisible == visible)
693 return;
694
695 cursorVisible = visible;
696 updateCursorBlinking();
697
698 if (cursorVisible)
699 connect(sender: QGuiApplication::styleHints(), signal: &QStyleHints::cursorFlashTimeChanged, receiverPrivate: this, slot: &QWidgetTextControlPrivate::updateCursorBlinking);
700 else
701 disconnect(sender: QGuiApplication::styleHints(), signal: &QStyleHints::cursorFlashTimeChanged, receiverPrivate: this, slot: &QWidgetTextControlPrivate::updateCursorBlinking);
702}
703
704void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::updateCursorBlinking()
705{
706 cursorBlinkTimer.stop();
707 if (cursorVisible) {
708 int flashTime = QGuiApplication::styleHints()->cursorFlashTime();
709 if (flashTime >= 2)
710 cursorBlinkTimer.start(msec: flashTime / 2, obj: q_func());
711 }
712
713 cursorOn = cursorVisible;
714 repaintCursor();
715}
716
717void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::extendWordwiseSelection(int suggestedNewPosition, qreal mouseXPosition)
718{
719 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
720
721 // if inside the initial selected word keep that
722 if (suggestedNewPosition >= selectedWordOnDoubleClick.selectionStart()
723 && suggestedNewPosition <= selectedWordOnDoubleClick.selectionEnd()) {
724 q->setTextCursor(cursor: selectedWordOnDoubleClick);
725 return;
726 }
727
728 QTextCursor curs = selectedWordOnDoubleClick;
729 curs.setPosition(pos: suggestedNewPosition, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
730
731 if (!curs.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::StartOfWord))
732 return;
733 const int wordStartPos = curs.position();
734
735 const int blockPos = curs.block().position();
736 const QPointF blockCoordinates = q->blockBoundingRect(block: curs.block()).topLeft();
737
738 QTextLine line = currentTextLine(cursor: curs);
739 if (!line.isValid())
740 return;
741
742 const qreal wordStartX = line.cursorToX(cursorPos: curs.position() - blockPos) + blockCoordinates.x();
743
744 if (!curs.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::EndOfWord))
745 return;
746 const int wordEndPos = curs.position();
747
748 const QTextLine otherLine = currentTextLine(cursor: curs);
749 if (otherLine.textStart() != line.textStart()
750 || wordEndPos == wordStartPos)
751 return;
752
753 const qreal wordEndX = line.cursorToX(cursorPos: curs.position() - blockPos) + blockCoordinates.x();
754
755 if (!wordSelectionEnabled && (mouseXPosition < wordStartX || mouseXPosition > wordEndX))
756 return;
757
758 if (wordSelectionEnabled) {
759 if (suggestedNewPosition < selectedWordOnDoubleClick.position()) {
760 cursor.setPosition(pos: selectedWordOnDoubleClick.selectionEnd());
761 setCursorPosition(pos: wordStartPos, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
762 } else {
763 cursor.setPosition(pos: selectedWordOnDoubleClick.selectionStart());
764 setCursorPosition(pos: wordEndPos, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
765 }
766 } else {
767 // keep the already selected word even when moving to the left
768 // (#39164)
769 if (suggestedNewPosition < selectedWordOnDoubleClick.position())
770 cursor.setPosition(pos: selectedWordOnDoubleClick.selectionEnd());
771 else
772 cursor.setPosition(pos: selectedWordOnDoubleClick.selectionStart());
773
774 const qreal differenceToStart = mouseXPosition - wordStartX;
775 const qreal differenceToEnd = wordEndX - mouseXPosition;
776
777 if (differenceToStart < differenceToEnd)
778 setCursorPosition(pos: wordStartPos, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
779 else
780 setCursorPosition(pos: wordEndPos, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
781 }
782
783 if (interactionFlags & Qt::TextSelectableByMouse) {
784#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
785 setClipboardSelection();
786#endif
787 selectionChanged(forceEmitSelectionChanged: true);
788 }
789}
790
791void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::extendBlockwiseSelection(int suggestedNewPosition)
792{
793 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
794
795 // if inside the initial selected line keep that
796 if (suggestedNewPosition >= selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.selectionStart()
797 && suggestedNewPosition <= selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.selectionEnd()) {
798 q->setTextCursor(cursor: selectedBlockOnTrippleClick);
799 return;
800 }
801
802 if (suggestedNewPosition < selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.position()) {
803 cursor.setPosition(pos: selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.selectionEnd());
804 cursor.setPosition(pos: suggestedNewPosition, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
805 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::StartOfBlock, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
806 } else {
807 cursor.setPosition(pos: selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.selectionStart());
808 cursor.setPosition(pos: suggestedNewPosition, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
809 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::EndOfBlock, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
810 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::NextCharacter, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
811 }
812
813 if (interactionFlags & Qt::TextSelectableByMouse) {
814#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
815 setClipboardSelection();
816#endif
817 selectionChanged(forceEmitSelectionChanged: true);
818 }
819}

983void QWidgetTextControl::processEvent(QEvent *e, const QTransform &transform, QWidget *contextWidget)
984{
985 Q_D(QWidgetTextControl);
986 if (d->interactionFlags == Qt::NoTextInteraction) {
987 e->ignore();
988 return;
989 }
990
991 d->contextWidget = contextWidget;
992
993 if (!d->contextWidget) {
994 switch (e->type()) {
995#if QT_CONFIG(graphicsview)
996 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMouseMove:
997 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMousePress:
998 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMouseRelease:
999 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMouseDoubleClick:
1000 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneContextMenu:
1001 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneHoverEnter:
1002 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneHoverMove:
1003 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneHoverLeave:
1004 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneHelp:
1005 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDragEnter:
1006 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDragMove:
1007 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDragLeave:
1008 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDrop: {
1009 QGraphicsSceneEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneEvent *>(e);
1010 d->contextWidget = ev->widget();
1011 break;
1012 }
1013#endif // QT_CONFIG(graphicsview)
1014 default: break;
1015 };
1016 }
1017
1018 switch (e->type()) {
1019 case QEvent::KeyPress:
1020 d->keyPressEvent(e: static_cast<QKeyEvent *>(e));
1021 break;
1022 case QEvent::MouseButtonPress: {
1023 QMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1024 d->mousePressEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->position().toPoint()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(),
1025 buttons: ev->buttons(), globalPos: ev->globalPosition().toPoint());
1026 break; }
1027 case QEvent::MouseMove: {
1028 QMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1029 d->mouseMoveEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->position().toPoint()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(),
1030 buttons: ev->buttons(), globalPos: ev->globalPosition().toPoint());
1031 break; }
1032 case QEvent::MouseButtonRelease: {
1033 QMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1034 d->mouseReleaseEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->position().toPoint()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(),
1035 buttons: ev->buttons(), globalPos: ev->globalPosition().toPoint());
1036 break; }
1037 case QEvent::MouseButtonDblClick: {
1038 QMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QMouseEvent *>(e);
1039 d->mouseDoubleClickEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->position().toPoint()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(),
1040 buttons: ev->buttons(), globalPos: ev->globalPosition().toPoint());
1041 break; }
1042 case QEvent::InputMethod:
1043 d->inputMethodEvent(static_cast<QInputMethodEvent *>(e));
1044 break;
1045#ifndef QT_NO_CONTEXTMENU
1046 case QEvent::ContextMenu: {
1047 QContextMenuEvent *ev = static_cast<QContextMenuEvent *>(e);
1048 d->contextMenuEvent(screenPos: ev->globalPos(), docPos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), contextWidget);
1049 break; }
1050#endif // QT_NO_CONTEXTMENU
1051 case QEvent::FocusIn:
1052 case QEvent::FocusOut:
1053 d->focusEvent(e: static_cast<QFocusEvent *>(e));
1054 break;
1055
1056 case QEvent::EnabledChange:
1057 d->isEnabled = e->isAccepted();
1058 break;
1059
1060#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
1061 case QEvent::ToolTip: {
1062 QHelpEvent *ev = static_cast<QHelpEvent *>(e);
1063 d->showToolTip(globalPos: ev->globalPos(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), contextWidget);
1064 break;
1065 }
1066#endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
1067
1068#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1069 case QEvent::DragEnter: {
1070 QDragEnterEvent *ev = static_cast<QDragEnterEvent *>(e);
1071 if (d->dragEnterEvent(e, mimeData: ev->mimeData()))
1072 ev->acceptProposedAction();
1073 break;
1074 }
1075 case QEvent::DragLeave:
1076 d->dragLeaveEvent();
1077 break;
1078 case QEvent::DragMove: {
1079 QDragMoveEvent *ev = static_cast<QDragMoveEvent *>(e);
1080 if (d->dragMoveEvent(e, mimeData: ev->mimeData(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->position().toPoint())))
1081 ev->acceptProposedAction();
1082 break;
1083 }
1084 case QEvent::Drop: {
1085 QDropEvent *ev = static_cast<QDropEvent *>(e);
1086 if (d->dropEvent(mimeData: ev->mimeData(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->position().toPoint()), dropAction: ev->dropAction(), source: ev->source()))
1087 ev->acceptProposedAction();
1088 break;
1089 }
1090#endif
1091
1092#if QT_CONFIG(graphicsview)
1093 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMousePress: {
1094 QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *>(e);
1095 d->mousePressEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(), buttons: ev->buttons(),
1096 globalPos: ev->screenPos());
1097 break; }
1098 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMouseMove: {
1099 QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *>(e);
1100 d->mouseMoveEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(), buttons: ev->buttons(),
1101 globalPos: ev->screenPos());
1102 break; }
1103 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMouseRelease: {
1104 QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *>(e);
1105 d->mouseReleaseEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(), buttons: ev->buttons(),
1106 globalPos: ev->screenPos());
1107 break; }
1108 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneMouseDoubleClick: {
1109 QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneMouseEvent *>(e);
1110 d->mouseDoubleClickEvent(e: ev, button: ev->button(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(), buttons: ev->buttons(),
1111 globalPos: ev->screenPos());
1112 break; }
1113 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneContextMenu: {
1114 QGraphicsSceneContextMenuEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneContextMenuEvent *>(e);
1115 d->contextMenuEvent(screenPos: ev->screenPos(), docPos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), contextWidget);
1116 break; }
1117
1118 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneHoverMove: {
1119 QGraphicsSceneHoverEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneHoverEvent *>(e);
1120 d->mouseMoveEvent(e: ev, button: Qt::NoButton, pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), modifiers: ev->modifiers(),buttons: Qt::NoButton,
1121 globalPos: ev->screenPos());
1122 break; }
1123
1124 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDragEnter: {
1125 QGraphicsSceneDragDropEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneDragDropEvent *>(e);
1126 if (d->dragEnterEvent(e, mimeData: ev->mimeData()))
1127 ev->acceptProposedAction();
1128 break; }
1129 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDragLeave:
1130 d->dragLeaveEvent();
1131 break;
1132 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDragMove: {
1133 QGraphicsSceneDragDropEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneDragDropEvent *>(e);
1134 if (d->dragMoveEvent(e, mimeData: ev->mimeData(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos())))
1135 ev->acceptProposedAction();
1136 break; }
1137 case QEvent::GraphicsSceneDrop: {
1138 QGraphicsSceneDragDropEvent *ev = static_cast<QGraphicsSceneDragDropEvent *>(e);
1139 if (d->dropEvent(mimeData: ev->mimeData(), pos: transform.map(p: ev->pos()), dropAction: ev->dropAction(), source: ev->source()))
1140 ev->accept();
1141 break; }
1142#endif // QT_CONFIG(graphicsview)
1143#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
1144 case QEvent::EnterEditFocus:
1145 case QEvent::LeaveEditFocus:
1146 if (QApplicationPrivate::keypadNavigationEnabled())
1147 d->editFocusEvent(e);
1148 break;
1149#endif
1150 case QEvent::ShortcutOverride:
1151 if (d->interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable) {
1152 QKeyEvent* ke = static_cast<QKeyEvent *>(e);
1153 if (isCommonTextEditShortcut(ke))
1154 ke->accept();
1155 }
1156 break;
1157 default:
1158 break;
1159 }

1202
1203void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::keyPressEvent(QKeyEvent *e)
1204{
1205 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
1206#ifndef QT_NO_SHORTCUT
1207 if (e == QKeySequence::SelectAll) {
1208 e->accept();
1209 q->selectAll();
1210#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
1211 setClipboardSelection();
1212#endif
1213 return;
1214 }
1215#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
1216 else if (e == QKeySequence::Copy) {
1217 e->accept();
1218 q->copy();
1219 return;
1220 }
1221#endif
1222#endif // QT_NO_SHORTCUT
1223
1224 if (interactionFlags & Qt::TextSelectableByKeyboard
1225 && cursorMoveKeyEvent(e))
1226 goto accept;
1227
1228 if (interactionFlags & Qt::LinksAccessibleByKeyboard) {
1229 if ((e->key() == Qt::Key_Return
1230 || e->key() == Qt::Key_Enter
1231#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
1232 || e->key() == Qt::Key_Select
1233#endif
1234 )
1235 && cursor.hasSelection()) {
1236
1237 e->accept();
1238 activateLinkUnderCursor();
1239 return;
1240 }
1241 }
1242
1243 if (!(interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable)) {
1244 e->ignore();
1245 return;
1246 }
1247
1248 if (e->key() == Qt::Key_Direction_L || e->key() == Qt::Key_Direction_R) {
1249 QTextBlockFormat fmt;
1250 fmt.setLayoutDirection((e->key() == Qt::Key_Direction_L) ? Qt::LeftToRight : Qt::RightToLeft);
1251 cursor.mergeBlockFormat(modifier: fmt);
1252 goto accept;
1253 }
1254
1255 // schedule a repaint of the region of the cursor, as when we move it we
1256 // want to make sure the old cursor disappears (not noticeable when moving
1257 // only a few pixels but noticeable when jumping between cells in tables for
1258 // example)
1259 repaintSelection();
1260
1261 if (e->key() == Qt::Key_Backspace && !(e->modifiers() & ~(Qt::ShiftModifier | Qt::GroupSwitchModifier))) {
1262 QTextBlockFormat blockFmt = cursor.blockFormat();
1263 QTextList *list = cursor.currentList();
1264 if (list && cursor.atBlockStart() && !cursor.hasSelection()) {
1265 list->remove(cursor.block());
1266 } else if (cursor.atBlockStart() && blockFmt.indent() > 0) {
1267 blockFmt.setIndent(blockFmt.indent() - 1);
1268 cursor.setBlockFormat(blockFmt);
1269 } else {
1270 QTextCursor localCursor = cursor;
1271 localCursor.deletePreviousChar();
1272 if (cursor.d)
1273 cursor.d->setX();
1274 }
1275 goto accept;
1276 }
1277#ifndef QT_NO_SHORTCUT
1278 else if (e == QKeySequence::InsertParagraphSeparator) {
1279 insertParagraphSeparator();
1280 e->accept();
1281 goto accept;
1282 } else if (e == QKeySequence::InsertLineSeparator) {
1283 cursor.insertText(text: QString(QChar::LineSeparator));
1284 e->accept();
1285 goto accept;
1286 }
1287#endif
1288 if (false) {
1289 }
1290#ifndef QT_NO_SHORTCUT
1291 else if (e == QKeySequence::Undo) {
1292 q->undo();
1293 }
1294 else if (e == QKeySequence::Redo) {
1295 q->redo();
1296 }
1297#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
1298 else if (e == QKeySequence::Cut) {
1299 q->cut();
1300 }
1301 else if (e == QKeySequence::Paste) {
1302 QClipboard::Mode mode = QClipboard::Clipboard;
1303 if (QGuiApplication::clipboard()->supportsSelection()) {
1304 if (e->modifiers() == (Qt::CTRL | Qt::SHIFT) && e->key() == Qt::Key_Insert)
1305 mode = QClipboard::Selection;
1306 }
1307 q->paste(mode);
1308 }
1309#endif
1310 else if (e == QKeySequence::Delete) {
1311 QTextCursor localCursor = cursor;
1312 localCursor.deleteChar();
1313 if (cursor.d)
1314 cursor.d->setX();
1315 } else if (e == QKeySequence::Backspace) {
1316 QTextCursor localCursor = cursor;
1317 localCursor.deletePreviousChar();
1318 if (cursor.d)
1319 cursor.d->setX();
1320 }else if (e == QKeySequence::DeleteEndOfWord) {
1321 if (!cursor.hasSelection())
1322 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::NextWord, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1323 cursor.removeSelectedText();
1324 }
1325 else if (e == QKeySequence::DeleteStartOfWord) {
1326 if (!cursor.hasSelection())
1327 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::PreviousWord, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1328 cursor.removeSelectedText();
1329 }
1330 else if (e == QKeySequence::DeleteEndOfLine) {
1331 QTextBlock block = cursor.block();
1332 if (cursor.position() == block.position() + block.length() - 2)
1333 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::Right, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1334 else
1335 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::EndOfBlock, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1336 cursor.removeSelectedText();
1337 }
1338#endif // QT_NO_SHORTCUT
1339 else {
1340 goto process;
1341 }
1342 goto accept;
1343
1344process:
1345 {
1346 if (q->isAcceptableInput(event: e)) {
1347 if (overwriteMode
1348 // no need to call deleteChar() if we have a selection, insertText
1349 // does it already
1350 && !cursor.hasSelection()
1351 && !cursor.atBlockEnd())
1352 cursor.deleteChar();
1353
1354 cursor.insertText(text: e->text());
1355 selectionChanged();
1356 } else {
1357 e->ignore();
1358 return;
1359 }
1360 }
1361
1362 accept:
1363

1370
1371 q->ensureCursorVisible();
1372
1373 updateCurrentCharFormat();

1391QRectF QWidgetTextControlPrivate::rectForPosition(int position) const
1392{
1393 Q_Q(const QWidgetTextControl);
1394 const QTextBlock block = doc->findBlock(pos: position);
1395 if (!block.isValid())
1396 return QRectF();
1397 const QAbstractTextDocumentLayout *docLayout = doc->documentLayout();
1398 const QTextLayout *layout = block.layout();
1399 const QPointF layoutPos = q->blockBoundingRect(block).topLeft();
1400 int relativePos = position - block.position();
1401 if (preeditCursor != 0) {
1402 int preeditPos = layout->preeditAreaPosition();
1403 if (relativePos == preeditPos)
1404 relativePos += preeditCursor;
1405 else if (relativePos > preeditPos)
1406 relativePos += layout->preeditAreaText().size();
1407 }
1408 QTextLine line = layout->lineForTextPosition(pos: relativePos);
1409
1410 int cursorWidth;
1411 {
1412 bool ok = false;
1413 cursorWidth = docLayout->property(name: "cursorWidth").toInt(ok: &ok);
1414 if (!ok)
1415 cursorWidth = 1;
1416 }
1417
1418 QRectF r;
1419
1420 if (line.isValid()) {
1421 qreal x = line.cursorToX(cursorPos: relativePos);
1422 qreal w = 0;
1423 if (overwriteMode) {
1424 if (relativePos < line.textLength() - line.textStart())
1425 w = line.cursorToX(cursorPos: relativePos + 1) - x;
1426 else
1427 w = QFontMetrics(block.layout()->font()).horizontalAdvance(u' '); // in sync with QTextLine::draw()
1428 }
1429 r = QRectF(layoutPos.x() + x, layoutPos.y() + line.y(),
1430 cursorWidth + w, line.height());
1431 } else {
1432 r = QRectF(layoutPos.x(), layoutPos.y(), cursorWidth, 10); // #### correct height
1433 }
1434
1435 return r;
1436}

1438namespace {
1439struct QTextFrameComparator {
1440 bool operator()(QTextFrame *frame, int position) { return frame->firstPosition() < position; }
1441 bool operator()(int position, QTextFrame *frame) { return position < frame->firstPosition(); }
1442};
1443}

1445static QRectF boundingRectOfFloatsInSelection(const QTextCursor &cursor)
1446{
1447 QRectF r;
1448 QTextFrame *frame = cursor.currentFrame();
1449 const QList<QTextFrame *> children = frame->childFrames();
1450
1451 const QList<QTextFrame *>::ConstIterator firstFrame = std::lower_bound(first: children.constBegin(), last: children.constEnd(),
1452 val: cursor.selectionStart(), comp: QTextFrameComparator());
1453 const QList<QTextFrame *>::ConstIterator lastFrame = std::upper_bound(first: children.constBegin(), last: children.constEnd(),
1454 val: cursor.selectionEnd(), comp: QTextFrameComparator());
1455 for (QList<QTextFrame *>::ConstIterator it = firstFrame; it != lastFrame; ++it) {
1456 if ((*it)->frameFormat().position() != QTextFrameFormat::InFlow)
1457 r |= frame->document()->documentLayout()->frameBoundingRect(frame: *it);
1458 }
1459 return r;
1460}

1552void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::mousePressEvent(QEvent *e, Qt::MouseButton button, const QPointF &pos, Qt::KeyboardModifiers modifiers,
1553 Qt::MouseButtons buttons, const QPoint &globalPos)
1554{
1555 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
1556
1557 mousePressPos = pos.toPoint();
1558
1559#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1560 mightStartDrag = false;
1561#endif
1562
1563 if (sendMouseEventToInputContext(
1564 e, eventType: QEvent::MouseButtonPress, button, pos, modifiers, buttons, globalPos)) {
1565 return;
1566 }
1567
1568 if (interactionFlags & Qt::LinksAccessibleByMouse) {
1569 anchorOnMousePress = q->anchorAt(pos);
1570
1571 if (cursorIsFocusIndicator) {
1572 cursorIsFocusIndicator = false;
1573 repaintSelection();
1574 cursor.clearSelection();
1575 }
1576 }
1577 if (!(button & Qt::LeftButton) ||
1578 !((interactionFlags & Qt::TextSelectableByMouse) || (interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable))) {
1579 e->ignore();
1580 return;
1581 }
1582 bool wasValid = blockWithMarkerUnderMouse.isValid();
1583 blockWithMarkerUnderMouse = q->blockWithMarkerAt(pos);
1584 if (wasValid != blockWithMarkerUnderMouse.isValid())
1585 emit q->blockMarkerHovered(block: blockWithMarkerUnderMouse);
1586
1587
1588 cursorIsFocusIndicator = false;
1589 const QTextCursor oldSelection = cursor;
1590 const int oldCursorPos = cursor.position();
1591
1592 mousePressed = (interactionFlags & Qt::TextSelectableByMouse);
1593
1594 commitPreedit();
1595
1596 if (trippleClickTimer.isActive()
1597 && ((pos - trippleClickPoint).toPoint().manhattanLength() < QApplication::startDragDistance())) {
1598
1599 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::StartOfBlock);
1600 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::EndOfBlock, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1601 cursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::NextCharacter, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1602 selectedBlockOnTrippleClick = cursor;
1603
1604 anchorOnMousePress = QString();
1605 blockWithMarkerUnderMouse = QTextBlock();
1606 emit q->blockMarkerHovered(block: blockWithMarkerUnderMouse);
1607
1608 trippleClickTimer.stop();
1609 } else {
1610 int cursorPos = q->hitTest(point: pos, accuracy: Qt::FuzzyHit);
1611 if (cursorPos == -1) {
1612 e->ignore();
1613 return;
1614 }
1615
1616 if (modifiers == Qt::ShiftModifier && (interactionFlags & Qt::TextSelectableByMouse)) {
1617 if (wordSelectionEnabled && !selectedWordOnDoubleClick.hasSelection()) {
1618 selectedWordOnDoubleClick = cursor;
1619 selectedWordOnDoubleClick.select(selection: QTextCursor::WordUnderCursor);
1620 }
1621
1622 if (selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.hasSelection())
1623 extendBlockwiseSelection(suggestedNewPosition: cursorPos);
1624 else if (selectedWordOnDoubleClick.hasSelection())
1625 extendWordwiseSelection(suggestedNewPosition: cursorPos, mouseXPosition: pos.x());
1626 else if (!wordSelectionEnabled)
1627 setCursorPosition(pos: cursorPos, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1628 } else {
1629
1630 if (dragEnabled
1631 && cursor.hasSelection()
1632 && !cursorIsFocusIndicator
1633 && cursorPos >= cursor.selectionStart()
1634 && cursorPos <= cursor.selectionEnd()
1635 && q->hitTest(point: pos, accuracy: Qt::ExactHit) != -1) {
1636#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1637 mightStartDrag = true;
1638#endif
1639 return;
1640 }
1641
1642 setCursorPosition(pos: cursorPos);
1643 }
1644 }
1645
1646 if (interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable) {
1647 q->ensureCursorVisible();
1648 if (cursor.position() != oldCursorPos)
1649 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
1650 _q_updateCurrentCharFormatAndSelection();
1651 } else {
1652 if (cursor.position() != oldCursorPos) {
1653 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
1654 emit q->microFocusChanged();
1655 }
1656 selectionChanged();
1657 }
1658 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection);
1659 hadSelectionOnMousePress = cursor.hasSelection();
1660}

1662void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::mouseMoveEvent(QEvent *e, Qt::MouseButton button, const QPointF &mousePos, Qt::KeyboardModifiers modifiers,
1663 Qt::MouseButtons buttons, const QPoint &globalPos)
1664{
1665 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
1666
1667 if (interactionFlags & Qt::LinksAccessibleByMouse) {
1668 QString anchor = q->anchorAt(pos: mousePos);
1669 if (anchor != highlightedAnchor) {
1670 highlightedAnchor = anchor;
1671 emit q->linkHovered(anchor);
1672 }
1673 }
1674
1675 if (buttons & Qt::LeftButton) {
1676 const bool editable = interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable;
1677
1678 if (!(mousePressed
1679 || editable
1680 || mightStartDrag
1681 || selectedWordOnDoubleClick.hasSelection()
1682 || selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.hasSelection()))
1683 return;
1684
1685 const QTextCursor oldSelection = cursor;
1686 const int oldCursorPos = cursor.position();
1687
1688 if (mightStartDrag) {
1689 if ((mousePos.toPoint() - mousePressPos).manhattanLength() > QApplication::startDragDistance())
1690 startDrag();
1691 return;
1692 }
1693
1694 const qreal mouseX = qreal(mousePos.x());
1695
1696 int newCursorPos = q->hitTest(point: mousePos, accuracy: Qt::FuzzyHit);
1697
1698 if (isPreediting()) {
1699 // note: oldCursorPos not including preedit
1700 int selectionStartPos = q->hitTest(point: mousePressPos, accuracy: Qt::FuzzyHit);
1701
1702 if (newCursorPos != selectionStartPos) {
1703 commitPreedit();
1704 // commit invalidates positions
1705 newCursorPos = q->hitTest(point: mousePos, accuracy: Qt::FuzzyHit);
1706 selectionStartPos = q->hitTest(point: mousePressPos, accuracy: Qt::FuzzyHit);
1707 setCursorPosition(pos: selectionStartPos);
1708 }
1709 }
1710
1711 if (newCursorPos == -1)
1712 return;
1713
1714 if (mousePressed && wordSelectionEnabled && !selectedWordOnDoubleClick.hasSelection()) {
1715 selectedWordOnDoubleClick = cursor;
1716 selectedWordOnDoubleClick.select(selection: QTextCursor::WordUnderCursor);
1717 }
1718
1719 if (selectedBlockOnTrippleClick.hasSelection())
1720 extendBlockwiseSelection(suggestedNewPosition: newCursorPos);
1721 else if (selectedWordOnDoubleClick.hasSelection())
1722 extendWordwiseSelection(suggestedNewPosition: newCursorPos, mouseXPosition: mouseX);
1723 else if (mousePressed && !isPreediting())
1724 setCursorPosition(pos: newCursorPos, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
1725
1726 if (interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable) {
1727 // don't call ensureVisible for the visible cursor to avoid jumping
1728 // scrollbars. the autoscrolling ensures smooth scrolling if necessary.
1729 //q->ensureCursorVisible();
1730 if (cursor.position() != oldCursorPos)
1731 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
1732 _q_updateCurrentCharFormatAndSelection();
1733#ifndef QT_NO_IM
1734 if (contextWidget)
1735 QGuiApplication::inputMethod()->update(queries: Qt::ImQueryInput);
1736#endif //QT_NO_IM
1737 } else {
1738 //emit q->visibilityRequest(QRectF(mousePos, QSizeF(1, 1)));
1739 if (cursor.position() != oldCursorPos) {
1740 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
1741 emit q->microFocusChanged();
1742 }
1743 }
1744 selectionChanged(forceEmitSelectionChanged: true);
1745 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection);
1746 } else {
1747 bool wasValid = blockWithMarkerUnderMouse.isValid();
1748 blockWithMarkerUnderMouse = q->blockWithMarkerAt(pos: mousePos);
1749 if (wasValid != blockWithMarkerUnderMouse.isValid())
1750 emit q->blockMarkerHovered(block: blockWithMarkerUnderMouse);
1751 }
1752
1753 sendMouseEventToInputContext(e, eventType: QEvent::MouseMove, button, pos: mousePos, modifiers, buttons, globalPos);
1754}

1756void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::mouseReleaseEvent(QEvent *e, Qt::MouseButton button, const QPointF &pos, Qt::KeyboardModifiers modifiers,
1757 Qt::MouseButtons buttons, const QPoint &globalPos)
1758{
1759 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
1760
1761 const QTextCursor oldSelection = cursor;
1762 if (sendMouseEventToInputContext(
1763 e, eventType: QEvent::MouseButtonRelease, button, pos, modifiers, buttons, globalPos)) {
1764 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection);
1765 return;
1766 }
1767
1768 const int oldCursorPos = cursor.position();
1769
1770#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1771 if (mightStartDrag && (button & Qt::LeftButton)) {
1772 mousePressed = false;
1773 setCursorPosition(pos);
1774 cursor.clearSelection();
1775 selectionChanged();
1776 }
1777#endif
1778 if (mousePressed) {
1779 mousePressed = false;
1780#ifndef QT_NO_CLIPBOARD
1781 setClipboardSelection();
1782 selectionChanged(forceEmitSelectionChanged: true);
1783 } else if (button == Qt::MiddleButton
1784 && (interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable)
1785 && QGuiApplication::clipboard()->supportsSelection()) {
1786 setCursorPosition(pos);
1787 const QMimeData *md = QGuiApplication::clipboard()->mimeData(mode: QClipboard::Selection);
1788 if (md)
1789 q->insertFromMimeData(source: md);
1790#endif
1791 }
1792
1793 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection);
1794
1795 if (cursor.position() != oldCursorPos) {
1796 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
1797 emit q->microFocusChanged();
1798 }
1799
1800 // toggle any checkbox that the user clicks
1801 if ((interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable) && (button & Qt::LeftButton) &&
1802 (blockWithMarkerUnderMouse.isValid()) && !cursor.hasSelection()) {
1803 QTextBlock markerBlock = q->blockWithMarkerAt(pos);
1804 if (markerBlock == blockWithMarkerUnderMouse) {
1805 auto fmt = blockWithMarkerUnderMouse.blockFormat();
1806 switch (fmt.marker()) {
1807 case QTextBlockFormat::MarkerType::Unchecked :
1808 fmt.setMarker(QTextBlockFormat::MarkerType::Checked);
1809 break;
1810 case QTextBlockFormat::MarkerType::Checked:
1811 fmt.setMarker(QTextBlockFormat::MarkerType::Unchecked);
1812 break;
1813 default:
1814 break;
1815 }
1816 cursor.setBlockFormat(fmt);
1817 }
1818 }
1819
1820 if (interactionFlags & Qt::LinksAccessibleByMouse) {
1821
1822 // Ignore event unless left button has been pressed
1823 if (!(button & Qt::LeftButton)) {
1824 e->ignore();
1825 return;
1826 }
1827
1828 const QString anchor = q->anchorAt(pos);
1829
1830 // Ignore event without selection anchor
1831 if (anchor.isEmpty()) {
1832 e->ignore();
1833 return;
1834 }
1835
1836 if (!cursor.hasSelection()
1837 || (anchor == anchorOnMousePress && hadSelectionOnMousePress)) {
1838
1839 const int anchorPos = q->hitTest(point: pos, accuracy: Qt::ExactHit);
1840
1841 // Ignore event without valid anchor position
1842 if (anchorPos < 0) {
1843 e->ignore();
1844 return;
1845 }
1846
1847 cursor.setPosition(pos: anchorPos);
1848 QString anchor = anchorOnMousePress;
1849 anchorOnMousePress = QString();
1850 activateLinkUnderCursor(href: anchor);
1851 }
1852 }
1853}

2001bool QWidgetTextControlPrivate::dropEvent(const QMimeData *mimeData, const QPointF &pos, Qt::DropAction dropAction, QObject *source)
2002{
2003 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
2004 dndFeedbackCursor = QTextCursor();
2005
2006 if (!(interactionFlags & Qt::TextEditable) || !q->canInsertFromMimeData(source: mimeData))
2007 return false;
2008

2012 insertionCursor.beginEditBlock();
2013
2014 if (dropAction == Qt::MoveAction && source == contextWidget)
2015 cursor.removeSelectedText();

2019 insertionCursor.endEditBlock();
2020 q->ensureCursorVisible();
2021 return true; // accept proposed action

2026 Q_Q(QWidgetTextControl);
2027 if (!(interactionFlags & (Qt::TextEditable | Qt::TextSelectableByMouse)) || cursor.isNull()) {
2028 e->ignore();
2029 return;
2030 }
2031 bool isGettingInput = !e->commitString().isEmpty()
2032 || e->preeditString() != cursor.block().layout()->preeditAreaText()
2033 || e->replacementLength() > 0;
2034
2035 int oldCursorPos = cursor.position();
2036
2037 cursor.beginEditBlock();
2038 if (isGettingInput) {
2039 cursor.removeSelectedText();
2040 }
2041
2042 QTextBlock block;
2043
2044 // insert commit string
2045 if (!e->commitString().isEmpty() || e->replacementLength()) {
2046 if (e->commitString().endsWith(c: QChar::LineFeed))
2047 block = cursor.block(); // Remember the block where the preedit text is
2048 QTextCursor c = cursor;
2049 c.setPosition(pos: c.position() + e->replacementStart());
2050 c.setPosition(pos: c.position() + e->replacementLength(), mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
2051 c.insertText(text: e->commitString());
2052 }
2053
2054 for (int i = 0; i < e->attributes().size(); ++i) {
2055 const QInputMethodEvent::Attribute &a = e->attributes().at(i);
2056 if (a.type == QInputMethodEvent::Selection) {
2057 QTextCursor oldCursor = cursor;
2058 int blockStart = a.start + cursor.block().position();
2059 cursor.setPosition(pos: blockStart, mode: QTextCursor::MoveAnchor);
2060 cursor.setPosition(pos: blockStart + a.length, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
2061 q->ensureCursorVisible();
2062 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection: oldCursor);
2063 }
2064 }
2065
2066 if (!block.isValid())
2067 block = cursor.block();
2068 QTextLayout *layout = block.layout();
2069 if (isGettingInput)
2070 layout->setPreeditArea(position: cursor.position() - block.position(), text: e->preeditString());
2071 QList<QTextLayout::FormatRange> overrides;
2072 overrides.reserve(size: e->attributes().size());
2073 const int oldPreeditCursor = preeditCursor;
2074 preeditCursor = e->preeditString().size();
2075 hideCursor = false;
2076 for (int i = 0; i < e->attributes().size(); ++i) {
2077 const QInputMethodEvent::Attribute &a = e->attributes().at(i);
2078 if (a.type == QInputMethodEvent::Cursor) {
2079 preeditCursor = a.start;
2080 hideCursor = !a.length;
2081 } else if (a.type == QInputMethodEvent::TextFormat) {
2082 QTextCharFormat f = cursor.charFormat();
2083 f.merge(other: qvariant_cast<QTextFormat>(v: a.value).toCharFormat());
2084 if (f.isValid()) {
2085 QTextLayout::FormatRange o;
2086 o.start = a.start + cursor.position() - block.position();
2087 o.length = a.length;
2088 o.format = f;
2089
2090 // Make sure list is sorted by start index
2091 QList<QTextLayout::FormatRange>::iterator it = overrides.end();
2092 while (it != overrides.begin()) {
2093 QList<QTextLayout::FormatRange>::iterator previous = it - 1;
2094 if (o.start >= previous->start) {
2095 overrides.insert(before: it, t: o);
2096 break;
2097 }
2098 it = previous;
2099 }
2100
2101 if (it == overrides.begin())
2102 overrides.prepend(t: o);
2103 }
2104 }
2105 }
2106
2107 if (cursor.charFormat().isValid()) {
2108 int start = cursor.position() - block.position();
2109 int end = start + e->preeditString().size();
2110
2111 QList<QTextLayout::FormatRange>::iterator it = overrides.begin();
2112 while (it != overrides.end()) {
2113 QTextLayout::FormatRange range = *it;
2114 int rangeStart = range.start;
2115 if (rangeStart > start) {
2116 QTextLayout::FormatRange o;
2117 o.start = start;
2118 o.length = rangeStart - start;
2119 o.format = cursor.charFormat();
2120 it = overrides.insert(before: it, t: o) + 1;
2121 }
2122
2123 ++it;
2124 start = range.start + range.length;
2125 }
2126
2127 if (start < end) {
2128 QTextLayout::FormatRange o;
2129 o.start = start;
2130 o.length = end - start;
2131 o.format = cursor.charFormat();
2132 overrides.append(t: o);
2133 }
2134 }
2135 layout->setFormats(overrides);
2136
2137 cursor.endEditBlock();
2138
2139 if (cursor.d)
2140 cursor.d->setX();
2141 if (oldCursorPos != cursor.position())
2142 emit q->cursorPositionChanged();
2143 if (oldPreeditCursor != preeditCursor)
2144 emit q->microFocusChanged();
2145}

2147QVariant QWidgetTextControl::inputMethodQuery(Qt::InputMethodQuery property, QVariant argument) const
2148{
2149 Q_D(const QWidgetTextControl);
2150 QTextBlock block = d->cursor.block();
2151 switch(property) {
2152 case Qt::ImCursorRectangle:
2153 return cursorRect();
2154 case Qt::ImAnchorRectangle:
2155 return d->rectForPosition(position: d->cursor.anchor());
2156 case Qt::ImFont:
2157 return QVariant(d->cursor.charFormat().font());
2158 case Qt::ImCursorPosition: {
2159 const QPointF pt = argument.toPointF();
2160 if (!pt.isNull())
2161 return QVariant(cursorForPosition(pos: pt).position() - block.position());
2162 return QVariant(d->cursor.position() - block.position()); }
2163 case Qt::ImSurroundingText:
2164 return QVariant(block.text());
2165 case Qt::ImCurrentSelection:
2166 return QVariant(d->cursor.selectedText());
2167 case Qt::ImMaximumTextLength:
2168 return QVariant(); // No limit.
2169 case Qt::ImAnchorPosition:
2170 return QVariant(d->cursor.anchor() - block.position());
2171 case Qt::ImAbsolutePosition: {
2172 const QPointF pt = argument.toPointF();
2173 if (!pt.isNull())
2174 return QVariant(cursorForPosition(pos: pt).position());
2175 return QVariant(d->cursor.position()); }
2176 case Qt::ImTextAfterCursor:
2177 {
2178 int maxLength = argument.isValid() ? argument.toInt() : 1024;
2179 QTextCursor tmpCursor = d->cursor;
2180 int localPos = d->cursor.position() - block.position();
2181 QString result = block.text().mid(position: localPos);
2182 while (result.size() < maxLength) {
2183 int currentBlock = tmpCursor.blockNumber();
2184 tmpCursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::NextBlock);
2185 if (tmpCursor.blockNumber() == currentBlock)
2186 break;
2187 result += u'\n' + tmpCursor.block().text();
2188 }
2189 return QVariant(result);
2190 }
2191 case Qt::ImTextBeforeCursor:
2192 {
2193 int maxLength = argument.isValid() ? argument.toInt() : 1024;
2194 QTextCursor tmpCursor = d->cursor;
2195 int localPos = d->cursor.position() - block.position();
2196 int numBlocks = 0;
2197 int resultLen = localPos;
2198 while (resultLen < maxLength) {
2199 int currentBlock = tmpCursor.blockNumber();
2200 tmpCursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::PreviousBlock);
2201 if (tmpCursor.blockNumber() == currentBlock)
2202 break;
2203 numBlocks++;
2204 resultLen += tmpCursor.block().length();
2205 }
2206 QString result;
2207 while (numBlocks) {
2208 result += tmpCursor.block().text() + u'\n';
2209 tmpCursor.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::NextBlock);
2210 --numBlocks;
2211 }
2212 result += QStringView{block.text()}.mid(pos: 0, n: localPos);
2213 return QVariant(result);
2214 }
2215 default:
2216 return QVariant();
2217 }
2218}

2745bool QWidgetTextControl::findNextPrevAnchor(const QTextCursor &startCursor, bool next, QTextCursor &newAnchor)
2746{
2747 Q_D(QWidgetTextControl);
2748
2749 int anchorStart = -1;
2750 QString anchorHref;
2751 int anchorEnd = -1;
2752
2753 if (next) {
2754 const int startPos = startCursor.selectionEnd();
2755
2756 QTextBlock block = d->doc->findBlock(pos: startPos);
2757 QTextBlock::Iterator it = block.begin();
2758
2759 while (!it.atEnd() && it.fragment().position() < startPos)
2760 ++it;
2761
2762 while (block.isValid()) {
2763 anchorStart = -1;
2764
2765 // find next anchor
2766 for (; !it.atEnd(); ++it) {
2767 const QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2768 const QTextCharFormat fmt = fragment.charFormat();
2769
2770 if (fmt.isAnchor() && fmt.hasProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::AnchorHref)) {
2771 anchorStart = fragment.position();
2772 anchorHref = fmt.anchorHref();
2773 break;
2774 }
2775 }
2776
2777 if (anchorStart != -1) {
2778 anchorEnd = -1;
2779
2780 // find next non-anchor fragment
2781 for (; !it.atEnd(); ++it) {
2782 const QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2783 const QTextCharFormat fmt = fragment.charFormat();
2784
2785 if (!fmt.isAnchor() || fmt.anchorHref() != anchorHref) {
2786 anchorEnd = fragment.position();
2787 break;
2788 }
2789 }
2790
2791 if (anchorEnd == -1)
2792 anchorEnd = block.position() + block.length() - 1;
2793
2794 // make found selection
2795 break;
2796 }
2797
2798 block = block.next();
2799 it = block.begin();
2800 }
2801 } else {
2802 int startPos = startCursor.selectionStart();
2803 if (startPos > 0)
2804 --startPos;
2805
2806 QTextBlock block = d->doc->findBlock(pos: startPos);
2807 QTextBlock::Iterator blockStart = block.begin();
2808 QTextBlock::Iterator it = block.end();
2809
2810 if (startPos == block.position()) {
2811 it = block.begin();
2812 } else {
2813 do {
2814 if (it == blockStart) {
2815 it = QTextBlock::Iterator();
2816 block = QTextBlock();
2817 } else {
2818 --it;
2819 }
2820 } while (!it.atEnd() && it.fragment().position() + it.fragment().length() - 1 > startPos);
2821 }
2822
2823 while (block.isValid()) {
2824 anchorStart = -1;
2825
2826 if (!it.atEnd()) {
2827 do {
2828 const QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2829 const QTextCharFormat fmt = fragment.charFormat();
2830
2831 if (fmt.isAnchor() && fmt.hasProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::AnchorHref)) {
2832 anchorStart = fragment.position() + fragment.length();
2833 anchorHref = fmt.anchorHref();
2834 break;
2835 }
2836
2837 if (it == blockStart)
2838 it = QTextBlock::Iterator();
2839 else
2840 --it;
2841 } while (!it.atEnd());
2842 }
2843
2844 if (anchorStart != -1 && !it.atEnd()) {
2845 anchorEnd = -1;
2846
2847 do {
2848 const QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2849 const QTextCharFormat fmt = fragment.charFormat();
2850
2851 if (!fmt.isAnchor() || fmt.anchorHref() != anchorHref) {
2852 anchorEnd = fragment.position() + fragment.length();
2853 break;
2854 }
2855
2856 if (it == blockStart)
2857 it = QTextBlock::Iterator();
2858 else
2859 --it;
2860 } while (!it.atEnd());
2861
2862 if (anchorEnd == -1)
2863 anchorEnd = qMax(a: 0, b: block.position());
2864
2865 break;
2866 }
2867
2868 block = block.previous();
2869 it = block.end();
2870 if (it != block.begin())
2871 --it;
2872 blockStart = block.begin();
2873 }
2874
2875 }
2876
2877 if (anchorStart != -1 && anchorEnd != -1) {
2878 newAnchor = d->cursor;
2879 newAnchor.setPosition(pos: anchorStart);
2880 newAnchor.setPosition(pos: anchorEnd, mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
2881 return true;
2882 }
2883
2884 return false;
2885}

2887void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::activateLinkUnderCursor(QString href)
2888{
2889 QTextCursor oldCursor = cursor;
2890
2891 if (href.isEmpty()) {
2892 QTextCursor tmp = cursor;
2893 if (tmp.selectionStart() != tmp.position())
2894 tmp.setPosition(pos: tmp.selectionStart());
2895 tmp.movePosition(op: QTextCursor::NextCharacter);
2896 href = tmp.charFormat().anchorHref();
2897 }
2898 if (href.isEmpty())
2899 return;
2900
2901 if (!cursor.hasSelection()) {
2902 QTextBlock block = cursor.block();
2903 const int cursorPos = cursor.position();
2904
2905 QTextBlock::Iterator it = block.begin();
2906 QTextBlock::Iterator linkFragment;
2907
2908 for (; !it.atEnd(); ++it) {
2909 QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2910 const int fragmentPos = fragment.position();

2912 fragmentPos + fragment.length() > cursorPos) {

2914 break;
2915 }
2916 }
2917
2918 if (!linkFragment.atEnd()) {
2919 it = linkFragment;
2920 cursor.setPosition(pos: it.fragment().position());

2922 do {
2923 --it;
2924 QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2925 if (fragment.charFormat().anchorHref() != href)
2926 break;
2927 cursor.setPosition(pos: fragment.position());
2928 } while (it != block.begin());
2929 }
2930
2931 for (it = linkFragment; !it.atEnd(); ++it) {
2932 QTextFragment fragment = it.fragment();
2933 if (fragment.charFormat().anchorHref() != href)
2934 break;
2935 cursor.setPosition(pos: fragment.position() + fragment.length(), mode: QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);
2936 }
2937 }
2938 }
2939
2940 if (hasFocus) {
2941 cursorIsFocusIndicator = true;
2942 } else {
2943 cursorIsFocusIndicator = false;
2944 cursor.clearSelection();
2945 }
2946 repaintOldAndNewSelection(oldSelection: oldCursor);
2947
2948#ifndef QT_NO_DESKTOPSERVICES
2949 if (openExternalLinks)
2950 QDesktopServices::openUrl(url: href);
2951 else
2952#endif

3185
3186void QWidgetTextControlPrivate::insertParagraphSeparator()
3187{
3188 // clear blockFormat properties that the user is unlikely to want duplicated:
3189 // - don't insert <hr/> automatically
3190 // - the next paragraph after a heading should be a normal paragraph
3191 // - remove the bottom margin from the last list item before appending
3192 // - the next checklist item after a checked item should be unchecked
3193 auto blockFmt = cursor.blockFormat();
3194 auto charFmt = cursor.charFormat();
3195 blockFmt.clearProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::BlockTrailingHorizontalRulerWidth);
3196 if (blockFmt.hasProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::HeadingLevel)) {
3197 blockFmt.clearProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::HeadingLevel);
3198 charFmt = QTextCharFormat();
3199 }
3200 if (cursor.currentList()) {
3201 auto existingFmt = cursor.blockFormat();
3202 existingFmt.clearProperty(propertyId: QTextBlockFormat::BlockBottomMargin);
3203 cursor.setBlockFormat(existingFmt);
3204 if (blockFmt.marker() == QTextBlockFormat::MarkerType::Checked)
3205 blockFmt.setMarker(QTextBlockFormat::MarkerType::Unchecked);
3206 }
3207
3208 // After a blank line, reset block and char formats. I.e. you can end a list,
3209 // block quote, etc. by hitting enter twice, and get back to normal paragraph style.
3210 if (cursor.block().text().isEmpty() &&
3211 !cursor.blockFormat().hasProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::BlockTrailingHorizontalRulerWidth) &&
3212 !cursor.blockFormat().hasProperty(propertyId: QTextFormat::BlockCodeLanguage)) {
3213 blockFmt = QTextBlockFormat();
3214 const bool blockFmtChanged = (cursor.blockFormat() != blockFmt);
3215 charFmt = QTextCharFormat();
3216 cursor.setBlockFormat(blockFmt);
3217 cursor.setCharFormat(charFmt);
3218 // If the user hit enter twice just to get back to default format,
3219 // don't actually insert a new block. But if the user then hits enter
3220 // yet again, the block format will not change, so we will insert a block.
3221 // This is what many word processors do.
3222 if (blockFmtChanged)
3223 return;
3224 }
3225
3226 cursor.insertBlock(format: blockFmt, charFormat: charFmt);
3227}

3425void QUnicodeControlCharacterMenu::menuActionTriggered()
3426{
3427 QAction *a = qobject_cast<QAction *>(object: sender());
3428 int idx = actions().indexOf(t: a);
3429 if (idx < 0 || idx >= NUM_CONTROL_CHARACTERS)
3430 return;
3431 QChar c(qt_controlCharacters[idx].character);
3432 QString str(c);
3433
3434#if QT_CONFIG(textedit)
3435 if (QTextEdit *edit = qobject_cast<QTextEdit *>(object: editWidget)) {
3436 edit->insertPlainText(text: str);
3437 return;
3438 }
3439#endif
3440 if (QWidgetTextControl *control = qobject_cast<QWidgetTextControl *>(object: editWidget)) {
3441 control->insertPlainText(text: str);
3442 }
3443#if QT_CONFIG(lineedit)
3444 if (QLineEdit *edit = qobject_cast<QLineEdit *>(object: editWidget)) {
3445 edit->insert(str);
3446 return;
3447 }
3448#endif
3449}

3474void QTextEditMimeData::setup() const
3475{
3476 QTextEditMimeData *that = const_cast<QTextEditMimeData *>(this);
3477#ifndef QT_NO_TEXTHTMLPARSER
3478 that->setData(mimetype: "text/html"_L1, data: fragment.toHtml().toUtf8());
3479#endif
3480#if QT_CONFIG(textmarkdownwriter)
3481 that->setData(mimetype: "text/markdown"_L1, data: fragment.toMarkdown().toUtf8());
3482#endif
3483#ifndef QT_NO_TEXTODFWRITER
3484 {
3485 QBuffer buffer;
3486 QTextDocumentWriter writer(&buffer, "ODF");
3487 writer.write(fragment);
3488 buffer.close();
3489 that->setData(mimetype: "application/vnd.oasis.opendocument.text"_L1, data: buffer.data());
3490 }
3491#endif
3492 that->setText(fragment.toPlainText());
3493 fragment = QTextDocumentFragment();
3494}
